    <p>
      <m>{\textbf{Learning point}}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
      The figure formed resembles a rectangle.
    </p>
    <p>
      The length of the rectangle is almost equal to <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> 
      thecircumference of the circle, while the width is almost equal to 
      to the radius of the circle.
    </p>

    <image source="/Circle.png" width="50%">
      <shortdescription>explanation</shortdescription>
    </image>
    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow>\text{The area of the rectangle } =\amp \text{Length} \times \text{Width} </mrow>
         <mrow>= \amp \frac{1}{2}\, \text{circumference} \times \text{ radius}</mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
    <p>
      The circumference of a circle is <m>2 \pi r</m>. This means that 
      the length of the rectangle. is <me>\frac{1}{2} \times 2 \pi r=\pi r</me>
    </p>
    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow> \text{The area of the circle }=\amp \pi r \times r </mrow>
        <mrow> =\amp {\color{blue} \pi r^2} </mrow>
      </md>
    </p>

